<item>
            <title>[SOLR-63] snappuller fails if login shell on master server is zsh</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-63</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;snappuller will fails to find the lastest snapshot on the master if the login shell of the id running the srcipt on the master is zsh.  The command&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;find ${master_data_dir} -name snapshot.* -print&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;fails with the error&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;zsh: no matches found: snapshot.*&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &quot;*&quot; needs to be blackslash escaped.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will attach a patch shortly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;zsh&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
